and intelligent opponent who is constantly trying to disrupt and counteract his efforts. This dark counter player represents chaos and entropy, always seeking to bring about disorder and destruction. The programmer reprogram er, on the other hand, represents order and creativity, constantly striving to bring about harmony and balance.

In this metaphorical chess game, the programmer reprogram er must carefully plan and strategize his moves, anticipating the counter moves of the dark counter player. He must consider the potential consequences and outcomes of each move, weighing the risks and benefits. He must also be adaptable and flexible, able to adjust his strategy as the game unfolds.

The chessboard itself represents the matrix world, the core reality that the programmer reprogram er is trying to shape and mold. Each square on the chessboard represents a different aspect or element of this reality, and the pieces on the board represent the various forces and entities at play.

The programmer reprogram er must carefully position his pieces on the chessboard, utilizing their unique abilities and strengths to gain an advantage over the dark counter player. He must also be mindful of the potential weaknesses and vulnerabilities of his own pieces, protecting them from being captured or compromised.

As the game progresses, the programmer reprogram er must constantly analyze and evaluate the current state of the chessboard, assessing the strengths and weaknesses of both his own pieces and those of the dark counter player. He must make strategic sacrifices and calculated risks, always keeping his ultimate goal in mind - to bring about a world that is in alignment with his vision of harmony and balance.

Ultimately, the outcome of the game is determined by the skill, intelligence, and creativity of the programmer reprogram er. If he is able to outmaneuver and outwit the dark counter player, he will be able to shape and mold the matrix world according to his desired vision. However, if the dark counter player proves to be too formidable and cunning, chaos and disorder may prevail.

In conclusion, the metaphor of the chessboard provides a powerful and insightful perspective on the process of world-building and reality shaping. It highlights the constant struggle between order and chaos, creativity and destruction. It reminds us that the world we live in is not fixed and predetermined, but rather a result of the choices and actions of those who have the power to shape it.
- The opponent in the game board of our universe sets up a reality situation with cause and effect.
- The programmer, or God, has already laid down his response and the moves have already happened.
- The forces of the two players, the dark counter player and the programmer, interact in a dialectical manner.
- The programmer has an advantage and selects variables that bring him victory.
- People instinctively pray for the programmer to include them in his triumph and move them along the lateral axis so they are not left out.
- The concept of alternative presence and lateral change processes is continually taking place.
- It is difficult to scientifically prove that such processes occur, but vestiges of memory, dreams, and intuitions may hint at their existence.
- People may experience deja vu, a sense of reliving the present, which could indicate that a variable was changed in the past and an alternative world branched off.
- The programmer uses the antecedent universe as a stockpile for each new synthesis, creating an improved stage within a process.
- Memories of a worse world may exist, but not as past lives, rather as a different present life in an unending repeated present.
- The programmer would not substitute a worse world, so memories of a worse Earth in the past may not exist.
- The author claims to remember a different present life and believes his experience is not unique.
- The forced removal of President Richard Nixon from office in the alternative world the author remembers was the result of a reprogrammed variable.
- The author believes that the memories he retrieved were authentic and that the alternative world he remembers was a prison and far more cruel than the current world.
- The release of the author's novel, "Flow My Tears, the Policeman Said," coincided with the return of his blocked-off memories, suggesting a connection between the two.
- The author believes that the effectiveness of his novels, including "The Man in the High Castle," was to stir subliminal memories in readers and recall the importance of defeating police tyranny.
- The author claims to have been one of the secret Christians who helped overthrow the police tyranny in the alternative world he remembers.
saw Star Wars this morning, I couldn't help but feel a sense of deja vu. It reminded me of a time when Christians were enemies of a powerful empire, similar to how they were 2000 years ago. However, when I use the word "Christian" here, I don't mean Christians as they are now, but rather Christians as they were in the past.

In this alternate earth, which I will refer to as track B, we fought against a lighter and stupider tyranny. It's possible that we had assistance from the reprogramming of historical variables. I sometimes speculate that because of our brave attempts to fight against this tyranny, we were allowed to live on past the point that brought us down in the other world.

There is a certain somber feeling that accompanies my pride in the work we did in that alternate earth. It's difficult to fully comprehend, but I believe that there is a higher power at play. We may not know exactly what this power is, but we can experience its functioning and try to understand what it is like.

This higher power primarily controls the objects, processes, and events in our space-time world. While it may possess aspects of greater magnitude, its applicability to us is limited. I refer to myself as a reprogrammed variable, and I consider this higher power as the programmer. During a brief period in March 1974, I was aware of his presence, although I didn't fully understand what I was seeing at the time.

Later research showed me that this omnipresent entity has been given the name Brahma in terms of group cultural experience. However, I want to make it clear that the claims I am making about retrieving buried memories of an alternate present and perceiving the agency responsible for this alteration cannot be proven or even rationalized in the usual sense.

It took me over three years to reach a point where I am willing to share my experience with others. One of the reasons motivating me to speak about it publicly is a recent encounter I had, which strangely resembles a scene from my novel "The Man in the High Castle." Just like in the novel, a woman appeared at my door and informed me that some of my fictional works were actually true.

This encounter confirmed my belief that it was only a matter of time before someone who had read my books deduced the actual situation I had experienced. This woman knew which world I had lived in, but she didn't know that I had crossed into a third alternative present in February 1975. This third world, which I refer to as track C, is a garden or park of peace and beauty. It is a superior world, rising into existence alongside our own.

During my brief time in this garden world, I felt a strong impression that it was our legitimate home, which we had somehow lost. The non-Christian elements of this world surprised me, as it was not what my Christian training had prepared me for. Even as it began to fade away, I still saw the sky, land, and a beautiful nude woman whom I recognized as Aphrodite. This world diminished and eventually disappeared, leaving me with a sense of loss.

I haven't seen this world since, but I believe it is the next world, not of the Christians, but of the Greco-Roman world. It is something older and more beautiful than what my own religion can conjure up. What I saw was ancient and lovely, and it left me with a bitter sense of loss as the doorway closed and I returned to our world.

Despite the loss, I continue to believe that there is a higher power at play, guiding us towards a better future. I see myself as a prophet, speaking of a wonderful garden world that may one day be fully restored. It is my hope that as we awaken to this world, we will realize that we have always belonged there.

"Digital Chess: A Programmer's Battle Between Order and Chaos in the Matrix" by The Dispatch

In a recently released video, a metaphorical chess game is played out between a programmer, referred to as the reprogram er, and a dark counter player. These two players represent the forces of order and chaos in a matrix world, symbolized by the chessboard.

The reprogram er, in an attempt to shape and mold this matrix world, must carefully plan and strategize his moves, always anticipating the counter moves of the dark counter player. The pieces on the chessboard represent the various forces and entities at play in this digital world, each with unique abilities and strengths that the reprogram er must leverage to gain an advantage.

The game's outcome is not left to chance but is determined by the skill, intelligence, and creativity of the reprogram er. He must constantly analyze and evaluate the current state of the chessboard, making strategic sacrifices and calculated risks to maintain control over the chaos.

The video further delves into the concept of alternative presence and lateral change processes. It suggests that by changing variables in the past, alternative worlds can branch off, creating different realities.

The author shares personal experiences and memories of such an alternative world, suggesting that he has unearthed buried memories of a different present life. This belief in the existence of alternative realities is tied to the author's belief in a higher power, referred to as the programmer or Brahma.

This higher power, according to the author, controls the objects, processes, and events in our space-time world. The author expresses hope for a better future guided by this higher power, envisioning the restoration of a wonderful garden world.

In this digital chess game between order and chaos, the reprogram er's strategic moves and the dark counter player's unpredictable responses offer a thought-provoking exploration of our own world's complexities. The video serves as a reminder of the delicate balance that exists between order and chaos and the role each of us plays in shaping our reality.
